cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper involves natural language processing and planning, which are key areas of research in the sub-field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of a knowledge graph (KG) to facilitate effective planning and generalization suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves training a model to build useful graph representations, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve measuring the performance of the model, which could be considered a form of simulation and modeling (cs.SD).
